title: Bobcats finish third at Regina volleyball tourney
text:
Bobcats finish third at Regina volleyball tourney By: Uncredited Report Error 
The Brandon University Bobcats men’s volleyball finished third at the Cougar Invitational tournament in Regina on the weekend. 
Matt Powell had 21 kills, two blocks and eight digs in Sunday’s third-place match, which Brandon won 3-2 (25-16, 25-15, 22-25, 16-25, 16-14). Roy Ching added 15 kills, a pair of blocks and nine digs. 
hanlee McLennan and middle Jodie Baker. Breanne Sytnyk also had four stuff blocks. 
BU head coach Lee Carter gave court time to his newer players during the event and Brandon went 2-1 in the round robin before dropping Saturday’s semifinal 3-1 (25-19, 20-25, 25-17, 25-21) to the host Winnipeg Wesmen. Majewski led the Bobcats with 19 kills in that match. 
Both teams are off next weekend and begin conference play on Oct. 16 when they host the Trinity Western Spartans at the Healthy Living Centre.
